NCC Group plc - Strategy and SWOT Report, is a source of comprehensive company data and information. The report covers the company’s structure, operation, SWOT analysis, product and service offerings and corporate actions, providing a 360˚ view of the company.Features:Detailed information on NCC Group plc required for business and competitor intelligence needsA study of the major internal and external factors affecting NCC Group plc in the form of a SWOT analysisAn in-depth view of the business model of NCC Group plc including a breakdown and examination of key business segmentsIntelligence on NCC Group plc’s mergers and acquisitions (M&A), strategic partnerships and alliances, capital raising, private equity transactions, and financial and legal advisorsNews about NCC Group plc, such as business expansion, restructuring, and contract winsLarge number of easy-to-grasp charts and graphs that present important data and key trendsHighlights:NCC Group plc (NCC or “the group”) is a global information assurance services provider and offers escrow and verification, security testing, website performance and software testing services to organizations. The group primarily operates in the UK, Europe as well as in North America and Australia. It is headquartered in Manchester, the UK and employed approximately 721 people during fiscal year 2013.  The group recorded revenues of £99.2 million ($156.5 million) during the fiscal year ended May 2013 (FY2013), an increase of 13.1% over FY2012. The operating profit of the group was £19.8 million ($31.3 million) during FY2013, an increase of 70.6% over FY2012. The net profit was £14.5 million ($22.8 million) in FY2013, an increase of 90.2% over FY2012.Reasons to Purchase:Gain understanding of  NCC Group plc and the factors that influence its strategies Track strategic initiatives of the company and latest corporate news and actions Assess NCC Group plc as a prospective partner, vendor or supplierSupport sales activities by understanding your customers' businesses betterStay up to date on NCC Group plc’s business structure, strategy and prospects





